<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747145>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Aechmella filimargo Canu and Bassler; Eocene, late Jacksonian (= Priabonian), Sepulga River west bank, Escambia County, Alabama, USA; syntypes USNM 62585. (a,b) Syntype 2 showing autozooids and four avicularia marked by arrows. (c) Early astogeny in syntype 2 with ancestrula arrowed. (d) Syntype 1 with broken ovicell arrowed. Scale bars = 200 µm." ;
